# Root Cause Analysis â€“ Task 3

## Incident Type
Phishing email leading to potential credential compromise.


## 5 Whys Analysis

| Question                           | Answer                                  |
|------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------|
| Why was the phishing email opened? | User clicked the malicious link         |
| Why did the user click the link?   | Email appeared legitimate               |
| Why was the email not blocked?     | Email filtering missed the indicator    |
| Why did filtering miss it?         | IOC was previously unknown              |
| Why was the IOC unknown?           | Threat intelligence updates were manual |


## Root Cause
The primary root cause was reliance on manual threat intelligence enrichment, which delayed detection of newly emerging phishing indicators.
